      "content": "Attempting to taper off warfarin and self-determine dosages using garlic supplements or green juices is extremely dangerous and should never be done. Even tiny amounts of vitamin K-rich foods or garlic supplements can drastically reverse the blood-thinning effects of warfarin, leading to sudden, life-threatening blood clots. Because your doctor seems dismissive of your concerns, seeking a second opinion from a different specialist or joining a patient advocacy group could help you find better support. Please prioritize your safety over these unverified risks and insist on professional guidance before attempting any changes to your treatment plan.",
